Title:     ECCO Professional.
             (Arabesque Software Inc.) (The Best Products of 1993)(Brief
             Article)
Author:    Seymour, Jim


-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Full Text:

Picking the right PIM (personal information manager) isn't easy. Aside
from the usual requirements of ease of use, stability, and compatibility,
PIMs demand a match between styles: yours and theirs.

Version 1.1 of ECCO Professional ($395) may fill the needs and fit the
styles of more PC users than any other we've yet seen. At its heart, ECCO
is a sophisticated outliner. Literally everything in an ECCO file is part
of a master outline that you can expand for more detail or compress to
headings only. Click on items in that outline or on boxes on ECCO's menu
bar and you jump to two other ways of viewing that information: an
elaborate Rolodex-style contacts file, or an appointments-and-reminders
file, with daily, weekly and monthly views. As you would expect, ECCO
lets you link data among these files so that you can click your way
through the displays, chasing down related information. A cute
cursor-like "shooter" allows easy export of ECCO information. If PIMs
have disappointed you in the past, give ECCO Professional a look.

Arabesque Software Inc., 2340 130th Ave. NE, Bellevue, WA 98005;
800-457-4243. Version 1.0 reviewed: September 14, 1993, page 50.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Type:      Cover Story
Company:   Arabesque Software Inc.
Product:   Ecco Professional (Personal information management system)
Topic:     Personal information management systems
