Title:     The ultimate PIM? Ecco does it all.
             (Arabesque Software's Ecco Simplicity 1.1 and Ecco
             Professional 1.1 personal information managers)  (New!)
Author:    Brenesal, Barry


Abstract:  Arabesque Software's $395 Ecco Professional and $149 Ecco
           Simplicity personal information managers (PIMs) are strong and
           unique packages. The packages use outline views in place of
           the typical database to provide better organization. Outlines
           can have innumerable levels to provide users who like outlines
           an intuitive organization method. The interface handles block
           commands well, enabling users to move sections of their
           outlines while maintaining the relationships among the
           elements. The Shooter background program enables users to copy
           information to and from other packages. Ecco Professional also
           has folders to improve organization further. Each outline is
           automatically placed in a folder, and users can drag elements
           into multiple folders. Ecco Professional also enables users to
           add columns to outlines and to specify items such as views and
           folders for shared network use.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Full Text:

Everybody has his or her own vision of utopia. And everybody has a dream
personal information manager (PIM). Many of the current PIMs take the
contact-manager approach: They're basically special-purpose databases
designed to store names, dates, and addresses. These products--including
Prisma Software's YourWay and Chronos Software's Who-What-When--aren't as
good at managing informal collections of data and unstructured ideas.

Arabesque Software's two PIMs, Ecco Simplicity and

Ecco Professional, are a strong departure from the database-style PIMs on
the market. Both Ecco Simplicity and Ecco Professional have
well-designed, easy-to-use phone book and calendar modules, but they
replace the standard PIM's small, frequently unsearchable memo fields
with flexible outline views. Outlines are inherently superior to
databases as a planning tool because they conform to natural hierarchical
thought processes. With the Ecco products, you can create nearly
unlimited outlines using as many sublevels as you need.

It Works Like You Do

If you think in outlines, the implementation is intuitive. Hiding and
expanding outline levels is as simple as double-clicking on an entry
item. Block commands, used for manipulating nonsequential entries, are
handled particularly well. When you move items, the relationships between
parent items and subitems are always maintained. Included templates help
get you started with project planning and other basic tasks.

For quick-and-dirty links between programs, a small but useful background
program called Shooter enables you to copy information to and from an
Ecco program to any other running program.

Of the two Ecco products, Ecco Simplicity leaves off here. Simplicity's
older sibling, Ecco Professional, incorporates additional tools that
strongly enhance the product's capabilities.

Extreme Organization

Ecco Professional adds folders to the palette of organizational tools. A
folder is automatically created for each outline, and you can drag any
entry into multiple folders so it will show up in multiple outlines.

You can also add columns to any outline. Columns can contain dates, check
marks, plain text, or pick-lists (such as Important and Background).
Column values stay with the associated outline entry, and you can make a
column into an outline "parent" to quickly display all the entries marked
Important.

On a network, you can designate views, columns, folders, and forms for
shared network or private use, but password support is missing. Arabesque
plans to add group scheduling features to a later release.

The Ecco product line is integrated. Forms and columns created with Ecco
Professional are usable in Ecco Simplicity.

No other PIM can provide Ecco's combination of solid, traditional
modules, useful outline views, and OLE support. Competitor Lotus
Organizer has a cleaner, more instantly intuitive display, but it isn't
nearly as flexible. Note-based Info Select for Windows breaks the
database barrier, although it lacks an integrated calendar and phone
book.

Both Ecco Professional and Ecco Simplicity are strong PIMs. If your
information management needs are simple, Ecco Simplicity is a good value
at $149. Ecco Professional, with its amazing powers of organization,
justifies its higher $395 price tag. An upgrade from Simplicity to
Professional is $199. Ecco Professional 1.1 $395 Arabesque Software (206)
869-9600

Ecco Simplicity 1.1 * $149 * Arabesque Software * (206) 869-9600
